DESCRIPTION:'Romantics\, Punks and Revolutionaries\; A double-header of rad
 ical history and puppetry cabaret' THE MOTHER WOLF CLUB'S NSA QUOI (60 mins
 ) A punk puppetry cabaret featuring a barbershop trio of sweary eyeballs\, 
 a psychobilly skeleton\, and Arnie The Intolerant Toaster who finds new cre
 ative ways to get canceled every gig. From three-chord shoutalong hits you'
 ll learn that rebellion comes with a rulebook and anarchy with a uniform. S
 lide into their DMs and stomp down to this freakshow of fun. The Mother Wol
 f are a comedy troupe that has taken their surreal shows everywhere from Gl
 astonbury's Truth Stage to David Lynch's Club Silencio in Paris\, from Beau
 tiful Days and Bestival to Bulgaria’s Meadows in the Mountains. They have
  been hailed as “Irresistibly fun” (Reviews Hub) and “Hugely inventiv
 e" (Everything Theatre) PETE THE TEMP'S ROMANTICS\, MYSTICS & REVOLUTIONARI
 ES (60 mins) A performance lecture which blends scholarship with comedy and
